      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/47788.Michael_Shermer">About Michael Shermer</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/47788.Michael_Shermer"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1221964940p3/47788.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/47788.Michael_Shermer">Michael Shermer
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
950
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer9810511017658187371">Michael Brant Shermer (born September 8, 1954 in Glendale, California) is an American science writer, historian of science, founder of The Skeptics Society, and Editor in Chief of its magazine <i>Skeptic</i>, which is largely devoted to investigating and debunking pseudoscientific and supernatural claims. The Skeptics Society currently has over 55,000 members.<br/><br/>Shermer is also the producer and co-host of t</span>
  <span id="freeText9810511017658187371" style="display:none">Michael Brant Shermer (born September 8, 1954 in Glendale, California) is an American science writer, historian of science, founder of The Skeptics Society, and Editor in Chief of its magazine <i>Skeptic</i>, which is largely devoted to investigating and debunking pseudoscientific and supernatural claims. The Skeptics Society currently has over 55,000 members.<br /><br />Shermer is also the producer and co-host of the 13-hour Fox Family television series Exploring the Unknown. Since April 2004, he has been a monthly columnist for Scientific American magazine with his Skeptic column. Once a fundamentalist Christian, Shermer now describes himself as an agnostic nontheist and an advocate for humanist philosophy.<br /><br /><br />more info: <br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://us.macmillan.com/author/michaelshermer">http://us.macmillan.com/author/michae...</a><br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Shermer">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="9810511017658187371" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

